Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper investigates the behaviour of attention in neural models of visually grounded speech, which is a topic related to natural language processing and speech recognition. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper uses visual information to ground speech and investigates the behaviour of attention in neural models, which is related to computer vision and pattern recognition. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses neural models to perform visually grounded speech recognition and investigates the behaviour of attention, which is related to machine learning. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper uses artificial neural attention to perform visually grounded speech recognition and investigates the behaviour of attention, which is related to artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.SD (Sound) - The paper investigates the behaviour of attention in speech recognition, which is related to sound.
